            "draft_value": "Science Mission Directorate",
            "rationale": "Consistent with the 'Short Title' provided in the Reference Values for this programmatic request.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1241425694:8eacc774a9ac",
            "label": "Short Description and Justification of the Request",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Request $9,000,000,000 for NASA Science Mission Directorate to restore workforce stability and programmatic momentum following FY2026 funding disruptions\n* Sustains U.S. leadership in global space science against rapid expansion by international competitors like China, who are targeting Mars and Jovian exploration\n* Supports peer-reviewed scientific priorities identified in the National Academies Decadal Surveys, ensuring high-yield returns on federal R&D investments\n* Drives a 3-to-1 economic return by engaging the domestic industrial base and strengthening the national STEM talent pipeline",
            "rationale": "Uses the specific $9B ask amount and incorporates core advocacy talking points regarding American leadership, competition with China, and economic ROI as outlined in the reference values.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1087467434:69c6aa746f2a",
            "label": "Connection to AZ-03 or Arizona",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Direct economic impact in AZ-03 totaling $588,689 in NASA Science obligations between FY2023 and FY2025\n* Support for local high-tech employers including Avnet Inc ($304,743) and Jb Technical Support Service LLC ($137,975) for specialized aerospace research and machinery\n* Jb Technical Support Service LLC in Phoenix provides mission-critical maintenance for specialized chip bonding machinery used in spacecraft component manufacturing\n* Sustained funding ensures AZ-03 contractors remain part of the national aerospace supply chain that powers the mission toward Mars and beyond",
            "rationale": "Cites specific NASA spending data for AZ-03, including the total obligation amount and top contract recipients like Avnet Inc and Jb Technical Support Service LLC from the provided context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
